properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, fourth Pacific survey flight, first flight from San Francisco to Guam and back; fourth Pacific survey; identified by donor with additional information: "San Francisco - Honolulu, October 5-6; Honolulu - Midway, October 10; Midway - Wake, October 11-12; Wake-Guam, October 13".a. cover: green cachet at left with text, "First flight eastbound from Guam, Pan American Clipper"; purple cachet at right with text, "First flight westbound to Guam, Pan American Clipper"; three postmarks on front: October 5, 1935, San Francisco, October 16 1935, Guam, and October 24, 1935, San Francisco with football-shaped and wavy cancellations; two backstamps: October 5, 1935, Alameda, California, and October 13, 1935, Guam; three brown 6-cent postage stamps at upper edge; addressed to A.E.A. Bronson.b. information sheet: 8 1/2 x 11 with black text; additional information prepared by donor, including route information; flight cover was received mounted to sheet with photo corners.
properties.wof:name: airmail flight cover: Pan American Airways, Fourth Pacific survey flight, San Francisco to Guam
